<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9361> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9361" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 349" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7864> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7864" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis with L. Memmius (14) (see below). In MRR 2.446, and Index, 590, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.363, no. 349, 87 B.C.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7387> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7387" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See MRR 2.93, 98. Quaestor in 76 (or 77?) with his brother-in-law Pompey in Spain (Cic. Balb. 5; cf. Sall. Hist. 2.56 and 57M) and was probably under attack at New Carthage. He fell in the battle at the Turia in 75 (or 76?) (Cic. Balb. 5; Plut. Sert. 21.2; Oros. 5.23.12). On the dates, see below, on Cn. Pompeius Magnus (31) and Q. Sertorius (3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4388> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4388" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 76, Quaestors. Served under Pompey and fell in the battle on the Turia (Plut. Sert. 21.1; Oros. 5.23.12; cf. Cic. Balb. 5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4344> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4344" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Pompey in Spain (Cic. Balb. 5), where he attacked New Carthage (Cic. Balb. 5; see 75, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4343> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4343" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "3 Münzer (RE) shows clearly that this C. Memmius should not be identified with the Praetor of 58. For the opposite view, see Mommsen, RMW 597f.; Groebe in D.-G. 4.37 1, note 9; and Sobeck 36. He may have accompanied Pompey in 77 as Quaestor, and therefore be a Proquaestor in this year." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4329> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4329" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Metellus in Spain. See 79, Tribunes of the Soldiers." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4301> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4301" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 79, Tribunes of the Soldiers." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4277> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4277" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Caecilius Metellus Pius in Farther Spain (Cic. Balb. 5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4276> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4276" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "6 The sources give Memmius no title, but he served under Pompey, his brother-in-law, in Spain in 76 as Quaestor (see 76, Quaestors)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4225> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4225" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Placed in charge of Sicily by Pompey when he began his campaign in Africa (Plut. Pomp. 11.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4224> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4224" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "6 See RE no. 7 on his relationship to C. Memmius, Pr. 58, and candidate for the consulship in 54." .
